summary: The customer is frustrated that their issue hasn't been resolved and they have been unable to get through by phone. The agent finds that there have been three complaints; one for a coupon, one for a biscuit, and one for a replacement. The agent offers to help the customer by putting them in touch with the local team and staying on the line to help with any language issues. The customer is informed that there has been no call from the local team in the last 15-20 days and is asked to provide a callback number should the local team need to contact them.
speaker_a_summary: A customer named Mr. Ram Lal called the ITC regarding three complaints he had made, and he is dissatisfied that they still have not been resolved. The customer service representative, Akash, apologizes and states that one of the complaints, regarding a replaced coupon, had been resolved by their executive. The other two complaints pertain to an issue with a food product and an issue with a faulty phone. Akash offers Mr. Ram Lal apologies and an update on the phone issue, and offers to look into the issue with the food product. The call concludes with Mr. Ram Lal accepting the updates and thanking Akash for his help.
speaker_b_summary: The speaker is trying to contact Monika but has been unable to speak to her. They are asking for her to call them back as there is an issue with a delivery that they ordered. They indicate that they have tried to call Monika multiple times and that other people also tried to call her on their behalf but there has been no answer.
cohere_points:
- Monika calls ITC to follow up a call she made previously regarding an issue she had.
- She did not receive any goods and would like to know the status.
- She is put on hold so the agent can check and confirm the issue.
- She is informed that the issue has not been resolved yet and the agent will help her. 
- She is informed that the agent will look into the issue.
